
Overview of verb straighten

The verb straighten has 6 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (7) straighten, unbend -- (straighten up or out; make straight)
2. (6) straighten, straighten out -- (make straight)
3. (3) straighten -- (get up from a sitting or slouching position; "The students straightened when the teacher entered")
4. (1) tidy, tidy up, clean up, neaten, straighten, straighten out, square away -- (put (things or places) in order; "Tidy up your room!")
5. roll out, straighten -- (straighten by unrolling; "roll out the big map")
6. straighten -- (make straight or straighter; "Straighten this post"; "straighten hair")
